<div class="row mb20">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <div class="col-md-12">
      <h2 style="font-size: 20px!important;">Entropion</h2>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      Name of Patient: <%=@patient.fullname.split(" ").map(&:capitalize).join(" ") %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-2">
      Sex/Age:   &nbsp;&nbsp;<%= @patient.gender %>/<%= @patient.age %>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <% patient_other_identifier =  PatientOtherIdentifier.find_by(patient_id: @patient.id.to_s)  %>
      <%if patient_other_identifier.try(:mr_no).present? %>
        MR No: <%=patient_other_identifier.mr_no%>
      <%else%>
        Patient ID: <%= PatientIdentifier.find_by(patient_id: @patient.id).try(:patient_org_id) %>
      <%end%>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-2">
      Date: <%= Date.current.strftime("%d/%m/%y")%>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-12">
      Son / Daughter of..............................................................................................................................................................
      <br>
      Address:
      <% unless @patient.address_1.blank? && @patient.address_2.blank? || @patient.city.blank? || @patient.state.blank? || @patient.pincode.nil? %>
          <%=  @patient.address_1 %>,
          <%=  @patient.address_2 %>,
          <%=  @patient.city %>,
          <%=  @patient.state %>,
          <%=  @patient.pincode %>
          <br>
      <%else%>
          ..............................................................................................................................................................................<br>
      <% end%>Tel:<%= @patient.mobilenumber%>
      <br/>
      I have been explained in my own language the risks and complications of surgery. I have also been fully explained the surgery is being done to correct my lid deformity and there will be no improvement in my vision.<br>
      <li>The complications which may occur are enumerated below:</li>
      <li>Infection and gape of the surgical wound</li>
      <li>Suture erosion, infection and granuloma formation</li>
      <li> Lid edema and scar of the incision</li>
      <li>Risks of corneal irritation, injury and ulceration</li>
      <li> Hemorrhage and haematoma formation</li>
      <li>Excessive watering / dry eye,</li>
      <li>Damage to the lid margin</li>
      <li> Loss of eyelashes</li>
      <li>Ptosis and lid retraction.</li>
      <li>A skin graft may be required to correct the deformity. I have been explained that:
      <ul>
        <li>The skin graft site maybe post auricular or the anterior forearm</li>
        <li>Graft rejection, infection, contracture or fibrosis may occur</li>
        <li>
      It has been explained to me that regular aseptic cleaning of the graft has to be done. It also has been explained to me that the
      donor site in case of a skin graft may gape or get infected and regular aseptic cleaning of the donor site is required.</li>
        <li>A tarsorrhaphy may have to be in place for 3-6 months to prevent contracture of the graft.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Chances of under correction overcorrection and resurgery have been fully explained.</li>



